	(uuid "6293f612-ad61-4760-ad66-c804a0624dd1")
	(paper "A4")
	(lib_symbols)
	(text "Animation Platter\n\nThis project is inspired by zoatropes. \n\nA NEMA17 stepper motor is used to spin an animation platter.\nAbove the animation platter is an array of many bright LEDs.\nThe LEDs provide the \"stroboscopic effect\" by strobing the\nlights at a frequency based on the frame count on the animation\nplatter.\n\nThe NEMA17 is driven by a TMC2209 silent stepper driver. The \ndriver is controlled simply via the enable, step and direction\npins.\n\nThe LEDs are driven by a mosfet. The output connector is supplied \nwith +12V supplied by VRx. There is also a neopixel output that\ncan be used for the strobe lights. The connector extends the \nneopixel line that already exists on the PCB.\n\nThe microcontroller on board is a STM32xxxxxxxxx. This was to \nmake transfering the code developed with a nucleo board easier.\n\nInterfacing with the system is done with three toggle switches,\nan encoder with a button, a potentiometer and a button. Status\nis indicated with several Neopixels and a four-digit seven-segment\ndisplay."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
